diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/streamlit/streamlit/pull/10071.patch","merged_at":"2025-05-09T16:16:25Z"},"body":"## Describe your changes\r\n\r\nToday, long Latex formulas overflow the page width, which looks weird and can make the entire app scroll: \r\n![CleanShot 2024-12-23 at 18 40 56@2x](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/fdcc1e48-f3b2-4f2e-97e3-5a5c8ce2896d)\r\n\r\nWith this change, we get the following behavior instead:\r\n![CleanShot 2024-12-23 at 18 40 14](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/e229940a-01af-433c-bc52-25e477fcf815)\r\n\r\nSpecifically:\r\n- Latex formulas that are in their own paragraph in `st.markdown` scroll horizontally. \r\n- Latex formulas created with `st.latex` scroll horizontally. \r\n- This doesn't touch Latex formulas that are inline with other text (e.g. `\"foo $formula$ bar\"`). I.e. these can still overflow and cause the entire app to scroll. I didn't touch this because it was a bit harder to fix nicely. I also think more and more we shouldn't fix that by controlling the overflow of the Latex formula but just preventing the entire app from scrolling horizontally. Anyway, I think this shouldn't happen very often anyway because inline Latex formulas are usually short. \r\n\r\n## GitHub Issue Link (if applicable)\r\n\r\nCloses #4304\r\n\r\nShould also update this forum post: https://discuss.streamlit.io/t/streamlit-latex-auto-wrapping-responsive-layout/7975/3\r\n\r\n## Testing Plan\r\n\r\nAdded e2e tests for the two cases above.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**Contribution License Agreement**\r\n\r\nBy submitting this pull request you agree that all contributions to this project are made under the Apache 2.0 license.\r\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/streamlit/streamlit/issues/10071/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/streamlit/streamlit/issues/10071/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null